article.headline: Wichita State 81, Evansville 65
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Paul Miller scored 14 points before fouling out, and P.J. Couisnard had 10 points and eight rebounds to lead Wichita State to a 81-65 win over Evansville Monday night in a Missouri Valley Conference matchup. The Shockers (12-2, 5-1) outscored Evansville (9-7, 3-5) 42-15 in the first half, led by Miller's 10 points. Evansville went more than seven minutes without scoring in the first half until Lucious Wagner's 3-pointer with 1:23 left made the score 40-13 -- a 21-0 run by the Shockers. Although the Purple Aces outscored Wichita State 50-39 in the second half, they never pulled closer than 16 points. Evansville shot just 22.7 percent in the first half, compared with 46.4 percent for Wichita State. But the teams ended up almost even in shooting for the game -- Evansville at 44.9 percent, and Wichita State, 45.3 percent. The Shockers also scored 30 points off turnovers, compared with 17 for Evansville. Wagner had 16 points to lead all Evansville scorers. Bradley Strickland added 11, and Kyle Anslinger, 10, for Evansville.
